                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File 838.00/587.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-21">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi> 21, 1911</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Furniss has been informed by the commander of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Petrel</hi> that unless he has information from Gonaives by the next day he
                    would leave for that place and would remain for 18 hours. Telegraphic
                    communication with Gonaives is interrupted, and the diplomatic corps considers
                    the presence of a war vessel necessary, as the Government is tottering.</p>
            </div>
